[
    {
        "source_sentence": "大般涅槃經集解卷第三十七",
        "translation": "Mahāprajñāpāramitā-sūtra Collection and Understanding, Volume 37",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c17_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　明慈悲有實益",
        "translation": "to show that kindness and compassion have real benefits",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c19_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　廣明慈心中布施發願事",
        "translation": "to explain in detail the act of making offerings and undertaking vows with kindness",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c20_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　廣明菩薩所脩之慈即萬行",
        "translation": "The love that is cultivated by the bodhisattvas consists of myriad practices.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c21_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　廣明慈益象見師子力士移石盧至長者斯那大多女人及提婆達多憍薩羅賊流離太子梵行品之第二迦葉菩薩白佛言世尊(至)如是之觀非虛妄耶。",
        "translation": "It's explained in detail that the Maitreya elephant saw the lion's strong man move Shilu up to the elder Senna, a large group of women, Devadatta Kauṣṭhila, Prince Lumbinī, and the second chapter of the religious practice of Kāśyapa Bodhisattva said to the Buddha, Bhagavān (until) isn't this contemplation",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c22_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c27_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c27_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第三門明四等。",
        "translation": "The third aspect explains the four and so forth.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c27_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "是實行也。",
        "translation": "This is the true practice.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c27_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "難有兩意。",
        "translation": "It's difficult to have two meanings.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c27_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此以虛行為難也。",
        "translation": "This is because it's difficult to practice in vain.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c28_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha school said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c28_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "難有三重。",
        "translation": "There are three difficulties.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c28_8"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此初重云。",
        "translation": "The first one repeats this, saying.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c29_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "眾生在苦。",
        "translation": "Sentient beings are in suffering.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c29_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不蒙救拔。",
        "translation": "They won't be saved.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c29_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "證慈非實也。",
        "translation": "He realizes that kindness isn't real.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0496c29_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "寶亮曰。",
        "translation": "Bao Liang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a01_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此下大段之第三也。",
        "translation": "This is the third major paragraph below this one.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a01_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "明慈是實行。",
        "translation": "It's clear that kindness is real practice.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a01_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "將辨此理故。",
        "translation": "It's because we're going to explain this principle.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a01_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "迦葉先作虛妄之難也。",
        "translation": "Kāśyapa first made a false objection.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a02_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此中凡六翻。",
        "translation": "These are the six translations here.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a02_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此下第一釋慈體是實行。",
        "translation": "Here, the first one explains that the essence of kindness is real practice.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a03_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "迦葉引五事。",
        "translation": "Kāśyapa cites five things.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a03_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "證其無實之難也。",
        "translation": "It's a difficulty to realize that it's insubstantial.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a03_8"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "世尊若非虛妄實與樂者(至)威德力故一切受樂。",
        "translation": "Bhagavān, if the Bhagavān doesn't give happiness in a false and real way (until) all receive happiness because of their authoritative power.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a05_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a06_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha school said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a06_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第二重難。",
        "translation": "The second difficulty is this.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a06_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "如其必益。",
        "translation": "As it will surely benefit them.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a06_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "是則眾生必應離苦也。",
        "translation": "Then sentient beings will surely be free of suffering.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a06_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若當真實不得樂者(至)云何得與此義相應。",
        "translation": "If they really don't attain happiness (to) how can they be associated with this meaning?",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a08_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a09_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a09_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此第二難。",
        "translation": "This is the second difficulty.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a09_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "明虛行不應得實報也。",
        "translation": "It's clear that false actions shouldn't obtain real rewards.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a09_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha school said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a10_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第三重難。",
        "translation": "The third difficulty is this.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a10_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以果驗因。",
        "translation": "It's the result of examining causes.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a10_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "二事相違。",
        "translation": "The second is the contradiction of things.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a10_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "虛實未辨。",
        "translation": "The false and the real haven't been explained.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a10_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "請求解釋也。",
        "translation": "It's also called an explanation.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a11_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛言善哉善哉善男子(至)諸佛菩薩真實不虛。",
        "translation": "The Buddha said, Good, good, good! Good man (until) the buddhas and bodhisattvas are real and not false.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a12_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a13_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a13_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "初偈說世間慈也。",
        "translation": "The first verse explains worldly kindness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a13_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "行人以施是實行。",
        "translation": "Practitioners use generosity as their true practice.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a13_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故以施福。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's because of the merit of giving.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a14_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "脩世間慈。",
        "translation": "He cultivates worldly kindness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a14_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不及其一況出世間也。",
        "translation": "It's not the same as a single condition that arises in the world.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a14_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "何者。",
        "translation": "What's that?",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a15_8"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "雖慈一人。",
        "translation": "Even though he's compassionate to one person.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a15_9"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "與世之樂。",
        "translation": "It's the same as worldly happiness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a15_10"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "施不得爾。",
        "translation": "That's not the case with giving.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a15_11"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "昇降可知矣。",
        "translation": "The rise and fall can be understood.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a16_12"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha school said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a16_13"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "就此明慈有實益門中。",
        "translation": "In this section, it's explained that kindness has real benefits.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a16_14"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "有五翻為證也。",
        "translation": "There are five translations that prove it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a17_15"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "初明脩慈實能轉境。",
        "translation": "The first explains that cultivating kindness really transforms objects.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a17_16"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第二明慈能斷煩惱。",
        "translation": "The second explains that kindness can stop afflictions.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a17_17"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第三明慈為萬善根本。",
        "translation": "The third explains that kindness is the root of all goodness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a18_18"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第四明慈即萬行。",
        "translation": "The fourth clarifies that kindness is the myriad practices.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a18_19"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第五引果地之慈。",
        "translation": "The fifth refers to the kindness of the fruition stage.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a19_20"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "證真實不虛也。",
        "translation": "It's the realization that reality is not false.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a19_21"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛是窮慈之極。",
        "translation": "The Buddha is the ultimate in limitless compassion.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a20_22"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "得知因地亦有實益也。",
        "translation": "Knowing the causal ground also has real benefits.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a20_23"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "雖可有此五翻。",
        "translation": "Although these five translations can be found, they're all different.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a20_24"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若欲對向三問者。",
        "translation": "If he wants to address the three questions, he'll ask them.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a21_25"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此五翻悉證慈有實益。",
        "translation": "These five translations fully realize that kindness has real benefits.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a21_26"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "並答初問。",
        "translation": "They also answer the first question.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a22_27"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "下當更題。",
        "translation": "The next one will be further titled.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a22_28"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第二問出別答也。",
        "translation": "The second question asks a specific answer.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a22_29"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此偈言。",
        "translation": "This verse says.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a23_30"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "慈之功用。",
        "translation": "The merit and function of kindness...",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a23_31"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "乃於諸行為勝。",
        "translation": "It's superior to all the practices.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a23_32"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "豈但實益而已。",
        "translation": "It's not just for real benefit.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a23_33"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不可以聲聞是虛。",
        "translation": "They can't say that śrāvakas are false.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a24_34"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "令菩薩益虛也。",
        "translation": "It causes the bodhisattva to benefit from emptiness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a24_35"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "二問既釋。",
        "translation": "The second question is to explain it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a25_36"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "則第三問自然釋矣。",
        "translation": "The third question then naturally explains it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a25_37"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "寶亮曰。",
        "translation": "Bao Liang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a25_38"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛將答難。",
        "translation": "The Buddha will answer the difficulty.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a26_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "先歎之也。",
        "translation": "First, he praises them.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a26_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "偈明實益格量功德。",
        "translation": "The verse explains the merit of the measured merit that's really benefited.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a26_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "何者。",
        "translation": "What's that?",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a27_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "有人止於一人邊與慈。",
        "translation": "Some people stop at the side of one person and give them kindness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a27_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "欲與其樂。",
        "translation": "They want to give them happiness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a27_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "始終必得出生死也。",
        "translation": "The beginning and end will surely attain birth and death.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a27_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "答人雖復供養無量五通神仙。",
        "translation": "Answer: Although people may also make offerings to the immeasurable five supernormal sages.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a28_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以為福田。",
        "translation": "They think it's a field of merit.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a29_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不如於一人邊起慈。",
        "translation": "It's better to give rise to kindness at the side of one person.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a29_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "十六分中之一也。",
        "translation": "It's one of the sixteen parts.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497a29_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "供養仙人。",
        "translation": "He made offerings to the sage.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b01_8"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "乃得生死之報。",
        "translation": "They'll then attain the results of birth and death.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b01_9"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若拔一人苦。",
        "translation": "Suppose he removes the suffering of one person.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b01_10"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "實獲出世之利也。",
        "translation": "They'll really attain supramundane benefits.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b02_11"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "又化無量人。",
        "translation": "It also transforms measureless people.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b02_12"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "得出於生死。",
        "translation": "He's freed from birth and death.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b02_13"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "當知慈是實也。",
        "translation": "You should know that kindness is real.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b03_14"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "釋慈有實益之義。",
        "translation": "He explains that kindness has the meaning of having real benefits.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b03_15"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "文齊於此。",
        "translation": "The text is the same here.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b03_16"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "云何知耶善男子菩薩(至)是實思惟非不真實。",
        "translation": "How do you know that good sons and bodhisattvas (arrive) are truly contemplating what's not unreal?",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b05_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b06_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b06_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "五事證慈。",
        "translation": "The five things are the realization of kindness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b06_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此第一明能令境雖不實。",
        "translation": "The first explains that it's capable of causing objects to be unreal even though they aren't real.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b06_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "而物得實益。",
        "translation": "Instead, things attain real benefits.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b07_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "如由金得樂。",
        "translation": "It's like attaining happiness because of gold.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b07_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "土即為金。",
        "translation": "Earth is gold.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b07_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若無金生樂。",
        "translation": "If there's no gold, happiness will arise.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b08_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "金即為土無異。",
        "translation": "Gold is the same as dirt without difference.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b08_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "小大相容。",
        "translation": "The small and large are compatible.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b08_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "當事皆實。",
        "translation": "These things are all real.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b08_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "而得其用也。",
        "translation": "They'll then attain its function.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b09_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "復次善男子云何名為(至)以是故名真實思惟。",
        "translation": "Furthermore, what's the name of good sons? It's because of this that it's called true contemplation.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b10_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b11_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b11_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第二以斷結。",
        "translation": "The second is to cut the bonds.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b11_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故知非虛。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's known that it's not false.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b11_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "復次善男子菩薩摩訶薩(至)阿耨多羅三藐三菩提。",
        "translation": "Furthermore, good sons, the bodhisattva Mahāsattva (to) attain supreme perfect enlightenment.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b12_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b13_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b13_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第三事以慈能生萬善。",
        "translation": "The third thing is that it's because compassion produces all kinds of goodness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b13_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "豈得非實耶。",
        "translation": "How could it not be real?",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b13_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha school said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b14_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "身被毒箭者。",
        "translation": "A person whose body is stung by a poisonous arrow...",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b14_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂慳貪箭也。",
        "translation": "It's the arrow of stinginess and greed.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b14_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "眷屬欲令安隱者。",
        "translation": "Those who want to make their followers peaceful.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b15_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "諸佛菩薩也。",
        "translation": "They are the buddhas and bodhisattvas.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b15_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "即命良醫而為拔箭者。",
        "translation": "He then ordered a good doctor to remove the arrow.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b15_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "令諸福田。",
        "translation": "It causes the fields of merit.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b16_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "往就乞也。",
        "translation": "He went there to solicit alms.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b16_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "且待莫觸者。",
        "translation": "Let's wait until someone who doesn't touch it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b16_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "方復優量。",
        "translation": "It's only then that it's superior in measurement.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b17_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "可施不可施。",
        "translation": "It can be given or not given.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b17_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "或財物多少。",
        "translation": "Perhaps it's the amount of possessions and property.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b17_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "時節可不也。",
        "translation": "The seasons and seasons may or may not.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b17_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "菩薩亦爾。",
        "translation": "So it is with the bodhisattvas.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b18_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若行施時者。",
        "translation": "If someone gives when they're practicing generosity.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b18_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "合譬也。",
        "translation": "It's a combined metaphor.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b18_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "復次善男子菩薩摩訶薩(至)常應勤發如是誓願。",
        "translation": "Furthermore, good sons, the bodhisattva Mahāsattva (to) always should diligently make such a vow.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b19_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b20_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha school said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b20_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "言依離身一尺六寸者。",
        "translation": "He says he relies on the one foot six inches from his body.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b20_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "如下經文。",
        "translation": "It's as follows from the text of the sūtra.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b20_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "又曰。",
        "translation": "Again, he said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b21_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "衣服離身四寸不墮。",
        "translation": "His clothes were four inches apart from his body and didn't fall down.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b21_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "便是一邊。",
        "translation": "It's one side.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b21_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "四寸四邊。",
        "translation": "It's four inches at the four sides.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b22_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "為一尺六寸也。",
        "translation": "It's one foot six inches long.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b22_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此則舉其四邊。",
        "translation": "These are the four extremes that are cited.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b22_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "彼乃言其一面耳。",
        "translation": "He then said, One side of it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b22_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子一切聲聞緣覺菩薩(至)以是義故實非虛妄。",
        "translation": "Good sons, all śrāvakas, pratyekbuddhas, and bodhisattvas (arrive) are really not false because of this meaning.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b24_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b25_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b25_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "六度是菩薩別行。",
        "translation": "The six perfections are distinctive practices of bodhisattvas.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b25_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "說施一事。",
        "translation": "It's said to be a single thing of giving.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b25_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "餘五可知也。",
        "translation": "The other five can be understood.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b26_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "其餘諸行。",
        "translation": "The other practices are likewise.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b26_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "與三乘共行。",
        "translation": "They're practiced together with the three vehicles.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b26_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "由佛說故。",
        "translation": "It's because the Buddha teaches it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b26_8"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以慈為本也。",
        "translation": "It's based on compassion as its root.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b27_9"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "先說人後說法。",
        "translation": "First, he teaches the person and then he teaches the Dharma.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b27_10"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不淨至無我等觀。",
        "translation": "It's the contemplation of impurity up to selflessness and so forth.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b27_11"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "說行相也。",
        "translation": "It's also called the mark of practice.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b28_12"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "燸法至見道修道。",
        "translation": "Up to the point where they see the path and cultivate it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b28_13"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "說得果深淺也。",
        "translation": "It's said to attain depth and shallowness of fruition.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b28_14"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "正勤至八聖道。",
        "translation": "They correctly apply themselves to the eight noble paths.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b29_15"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "說深淺法之名也。",
        "translation": "It's called profound and shallow dharmas.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b29_16"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "四禪至無諍三昧。",
        "translation": "The fourth dhyāna reaches the samādhi of no anger.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497b29_17"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "說定名也。",
        "translation": "It's called the name of concentration.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c01_18"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "他心智至佛智。",
        "translation": "cognition of other minds up to the Buddha's cognition...",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c01_19"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "說智名也。",
        "translation": "It's called the name of wisdom.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c01_20"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂皆以慈為本也。",
        "translation": "It means that they all have compassion as their root.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c02_21"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子能為善者名實思惟(至)如是無量無邊功德。",
        "translation": "Good sons, someone who can do good is called truly contemplating (up to) such measureless and limitless merit.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c03_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c04_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c04_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第四事說萬行即慈。",
        "translation": "The fourth thing explains that the myriad practices are called kindness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c04_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "除苦為慈。",
        "translation": "Removing suffering is called kindness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c04_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "三乘皆是滅苦。",
        "translation": "The three vehicles are all the cessation of suffering.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c05_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "要得實者。",
        "translation": "Those who want to attain reality...",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c05_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "則滅苦也。",
        "translation": "It's the cessation of suffering.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c05_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "思惟是慈。",
        "translation": "To contemplate is kindness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c05_8"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "盡苦名乘也。",
        "translation": "To end suffering is called the vehicle.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c06_9"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "迦葉菩薩白佛言世尊(至)所脩慈心為無利益。",
        "translation": "Kāśyapa Bodhisattva said to the Buddha, Bhagavān (to) cultivate a compassionate mind for no benefit.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c07_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c08_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c08_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第五事明慈。",
        "translation": "The fifth thing explains kindness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c08_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "現有實益。",
        "translation": "There's a real benefit in existence.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c08_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故發問。",
        "translation": "That's why he asked the question.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c08_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛言善男子菩薩之慈(至)是實思惟非無利益。",
        "translation": "The Buddha said, Good sons, the bodhisattva's kindness (to) truly contemplate is not useless.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c10_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c11_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c11_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "有二種必受苦。",
        "translation": "There are two kinds of suffering that must be experienced.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c11_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "一以不救故。",
        "translation": "One, it's because they aren't saved.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c11_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "二以雖得小樂。",
        "translation": "Second, it's because even though they attain minor happiness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c12_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "更增重苦也。",
        "translation": "It's even more painful.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c12_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂一闡提者。",
        "translation": "It's called an icchantika.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c12_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "夫定受苦報。",
        "translation": "They'll surely experience painful retribution.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c12_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "亦非但闡提。",
        "translation": "Nor is it just icchantika.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c13_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "餘業亦有。",
        "translation": "The other karmas are also present.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c13_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "而其相難辨也。",
        "translation": "Its characteristics are difficult to discern.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c13_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "受苦不定者。",
        "translation": "Suffering and suffering are indeterminate.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c14_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂與樂則得。",
        "translation": "It means to give happiness and then attain it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c14_8"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不與則不得也。",
        "translation": "If they don't give it, they won't get it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c14_9"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "遙見師子者。",
        "translation": "He sees the lion from a distance.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c15_10"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "夫不慈之物。",
        "translation": "A thing that's not compassionate...",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c15_11"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "有遇之者。",
        "translation": "If there's someone who meets it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c15_12"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "則便生懼。",
        "translation": "Then they'll become frightened.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c15_13"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "大悲之人。",
        "translation": "A person of great compassion...",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c16_14"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "有逆值者。",
        "translation": "There's the person who has a negative value.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c16_15"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "實自然生樂。",
        "translation": "They really naturally give rise to happiness.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c16_16"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以憑師有在也。",
        "translation": "It's because the teacher is present.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c17_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha school said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c17_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "前有兩關。",
        "translation": "The first has two aspects.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c17_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "同明慈有實益。",
        "translation": "They both explain that kindness has real benefits.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c17_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "已遣一關。",
        "translation": "He's already expelled one barrier.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c18_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "將顯事迹。",
        "translation": "It's about to reveal the facts and traces.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c18_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "是故迦葉重有前問。",
        "translation": "That's why Kāśyapa repeated the previous question.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c18_6"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛即釋。",
        "translation": "The Buddha is the explanation.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c19_7"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子我說是慈有無量(至)大涅槃經亦不可思議。",
        "translation": "Good sons, I say that this kindness has measureless (until) the great nirvāṇa sūtra is also inconceivable.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c20_0"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "It's a case.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c21_1"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c21_2"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "明法身無緣。",
        "translation": "It explains that the Dharma body has no conditions.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c21_3"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "有感斯應。",
        "translation": "There's a sense of this response.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c21_4"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以顯大慈之功無出入異者也。",
        "translation": "It's to show that the merit of great compassion has no difference between what comes out and goes in.",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c21_5"
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "大般涅槃經集解卷第三十七",
        "translation": "Mahāprajñāpāramitā-sūtra Collection and Understanding, Volume 37",
        "source": "T37n1763_037:0497c23_0"
    }
]